==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stop-over
<hw>Stop"-o`ver</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Permitting one to stop over; <as>as, a
<ex>stop-over</ex> check or ticket</as>. See <cref>To stop over</cref>,
under <er>Stop</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stop-over</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stopover</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stop-over
<hw>Stop"-o`ver</hw></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>the act or privilege of stopping over; stopping at a
station or airport beyond the time of the departure of the train or
airplane on which one came, with the purpose of continuing one's journey
on a subsequent train or airplane; the temporary interruption of one's
journey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a brief visit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoppage</ent>⟦br⟧
